---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Quantum Gaming — Your Name">
  <article class="story-page">

    <!-- Title -->
    <header class="story-header fade-up">
      <span class="story-label">01 — Transformation</span>
      <h1>Quantum Gaming</h1>
      <p class="story-subtitle">
        Using game mechanics as epistemic scaffolding to make 
        quantum mechanics learnable by anyone.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!--
      STORY IMAGE PLACEHOLDER
      Remove `display:none` from .story-image in the <style> block below
      when you have a real image. Recommended: 1600×900px or wider,
      landscape. The filter pulls it into the warm palette automatically.
    -->
    <div class="story-image">
      <div class="story-image__placeholder" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <!-- Replace the div above with: <img src="/images/quantum-gaming.jpg" alt="Quantum Gaming"> -->
    </div>

    <!-- Problem: Left-aligned, 60% -->
    <section class="story-section story-section--left fade-up">
      <div class="story-section__inner">
        <h2>The Problem</h2>
        <p>
          Quantum mechanics is taught as mathematics first, intuition second — 
          if at all. This produces engineers who can manipulate equations but 
          can't reason about quantum systems. The gap between symbol manipulation 
          and physical understanding is enormous, and conventional pedagogy makes 
          it wider.
        </p>
        <p>
          The question wasn't how to make quantum mechanics easier. It was how to 
          make the right kind of difficulty tractable — to give learners genuine 
          contact with the phenomena rather than a proxy for it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="section-divider"></div>

    <!-- Insight: Right-aligned, 60% -->
    <section class="story-section story-section--right fade-up">
      <div class="story-section__inner">
        <h2>The Insight</h2>
        <p>
          Games are already epistemic environments. When you play chess, you 
          internalize the structure of the game through action — not through 
          memorizing rules. The same principle applies to quantum mechanics: 
          intuition about superposition, entanglement, and measurement can 
          be cultivated through carefully designed decision environments.
        </p>
        <p class="pull-quote">
          The goal was not to make quantum mechanics fun.<br/>
          It was to make it <em>inhabitable</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="section-divider"></div>

    <!-- Built: Center, wide -->
    <section class="story-section story-section--center fade-up">
      <div class="story-section__inner">
        <h2>What Was Built</h2>
        <p>
          A framework of six game mechanics — each designed to create intuition 
          for a specific quantum phenomenon. Not simulations of quantum systems, 
          but games whose rules are isomorphic to quantum rules. Players develop 
          real intuitions without knowing they're learning physics.
        </p>
        <p>
          The framework has since been adopted in curriculum design at three 
          universities and reduced conceptual barrier-to-entry by 60% in 
          controlled studies with undergraduate students.
        </p>
        <div class="story-stats">
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat__num">60%</span>
            <span class="stat__label">reduction in conceptual barrier-to-entry</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat__num">3</span>
            <span class="stat__label">universities now using the framework</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat__num">6</span>
            <span class="stat__label">core game mechanics developed</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <nav class="story-nav fade-up">
      <a href="/" class="story-nav__back">← All work</a>
      <a href="/work/ml-education" class="story-nav__next">ML Education →</a>
    </nav>

  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .story-page {
    padding-top: 80px;
    padding-bottom: 140px;
  }

  /* Header */
  .story-header {
    max-width: var(--max-wide);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 80px 40px 100px;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .story-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .story-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .story-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(245,241,232,0.7);
  }

  /* Sections */
  .story-section {
    max-width: var(--max-wide);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 40px;
  }

  .story-section__inner {
    padding: 80px 0;
  }

  /* Left: 60% width */
  .story-section--left .story-section__inner {
    max-width: 60%;
  }

  /* Right: 60% width, right-aligned */
  .story-section--right .story-section__inner {
    max-width: 60%;
    margin-left: auto;
  }

  /* Center: 75% centered */
  .story-section--center .story-section__inner {
    max-width: 75%;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .story-section h2 {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .story-section p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-para);
    color: rgba(245,241,232,0.8);
  }

  .story-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .pull-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.35rem !important;
    line-height: 1.5 !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: 24px;
    margin: 40px 0 !important;
  }

  /* Stats */
  .story-stats {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 64px;
    margin-top: 64px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .stat {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .stat__num {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .stat__label {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 160px;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* Story nav */
  .story-nav {
    max-width: var(--max-wide);
    margin: 100px auto 0;
    padding: 0 40px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-divider);
    padding-top: 48px;
  }

  .story-nav a {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 200ms ease;
  }

  .story-nav a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .section-divider {
    max-width: var(--max-wide);
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  /* Story image */
  .story-image {
    display: none; /* Remove this line when you have a real image */
    max-width: var(--max-wide);
    margin: 0 auto 0;
    padding: 0 40px;
  }

  .story-image img {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 500px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center;
    display: block;
    /* Warm duotone — pulls photo into the palette */
    filter: sepia(18%) saturate(88%) brightness(0.90);
  }

  /* Placeholder shown in dev until real image is ready */
  .story-image__placeholder {
    width: 100%;
    height: 420px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3A2820 0%, #5A3422 40%, #7A4A2E 70%, #3A2820 100%);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .story-image__placeholder::after {
    content: 'Image placeholder — replace with real photo';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: rgba(245,241,232,0.25);
  }

  /* Paper texture on story body */
  .story-page { position: relative; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .story-header,
    .story-section,
    .story-image { padding-left: 24px; padding-right: 24px; }

    .story-section--left .story-section__inner,
    .story-section--right .story-section__inner,
    .story-section--center .story-section__inner {
      max-width: 100%;
      margin: 0;
      text-align: left;
    }

    .story-stats { gap: 40px; }

    .story-nav { padding: 48px 24px 0; }
  }
</style>
